POSIX_OPENPT(3)                                                                                     Linux Programmer's Manual                                                                                    POSIX_OPENPT(3)

NNAAMMEE
       posix_openpt - open a pseudoterminal device

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
       ##iinncclluuddee <<ssttddlliibb..hh>>
       ##iinncclluuddee <<ffccnnttll..hh>>

       iinntt ppoossiixx__ooppeennpptt((iinntt _f_l_a_g_s));;

   Feature Test Macro Requirements for glibc (see ffeeaattuurree__tteesstt__mmaaccrrooss(7)):

       ppoossiixx__ooppeennpptt(): _XOPEN_SOURCE >= 600

DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       The ppoossiixx__ooppeennpptt() function opens an unused pseudoterminal master device, returning a file descriptor that can be used to refer to that device.

       The _f_l_a_g_s argument is a bit mask that ORs together zero or more of the following flags:

       OO__RRDDWWRR Open the device for both reading and writing.  It is usual to specify this flag.

       OO__NNOOCCTTTTYY
              Do not make this device the controlling terminal for the process.

RREETTUURRNN VVAALLUUEE
       On success, ppoossiixx__ooppeennpptt() returns a nonnegative file descriptor which is the lowest numbered unused descriptor.  On failure, -1 is returned, and _e_r_r_n_o is set to indicate the error.

EERRRROORRSS
       See ooppeenn(2).

VVEERRSSIIOONNSS
       Glibc support for ppoossiixx__ooppeennpptt() has been provided since version 2.2.1.

AATTTTRRIIBBUUTTEESS
       For an explanation of the terms used in this section, see aattttrriibbuutteess(7).

       ┌───────────────┬───────────────┬─────────┐
       │IInntteerrffaaccee      │ AAttttrriibbuuttee     │ VVaalluuee   │
       ├───────────────┼───────────────┼─────────┤
       │ppoossiixx__ooppeennpptt() │ Thread safety │ MT-Safe │
       └───────────────┴───────────────┴─────────┘
CCOONNFFOORRMMIINNGG TTOO
       POSIX.1-2001, POSIX.1-2008.

       ppoossiixx__ooppeennpptt() is part of the UNIX 98 pseudoterminal support (see ppttss(4)).

NNOOTTEESS
       Some older UNIX implementations that support System V (aka UNIX 98) pseudoterminals don't have this function, but it is easy to implement:

           int
           posix_openpt(int flags)
           {
               return open("/dev/ptmx", flags);
           }

       Calling  ppoossiixx__ooppeennpptt()  creates  a pathname for the corresponding pseudoterminal slave device.  The pathname of the slave device can be obtained using ppttssnnaammee(3).  The slave device pathname exists only as long as the
       master device is open.

SSEEEE AALLSSOO
       ooppeenn(2), ggeettpptt(3), ggrraannttpptt(3), ppttssnnaammee(3), uunnlloocckkpptt(3), ppttss(4), ppttyy(7)

CCOOLLOOPPHHOONN
